Kerrville, Texas \| Louis Schreiner Field (KERV)

About Our Services

Provenarc Aero Solutions provides professional aircraft records digitization
services with white-glove concierge pickup and delivery throughout the
Texas Hill Country. Our 14-tier service menu addresses every stage of
aircraft ownership, from basic record backup to comprehensive fleet
compliance packages.

Every service includes:

-   Concierge pickup and return---no shipping carriers, ever

-   High-resolution scanning (300 DPI minimum) with OCR searchability

-   PDF/A archival format for long-term preservation

-   Encrypted delivery via USB drive and secure cloud download

-   Physical logbooks returned in archival-quality storage boxes

-   \$100K document insurance during transport

All pricing includes our concierge service within a 70-mile radius of
Kerrville. Extended travel available---contact us for custom quotes.

Tier 1: Digital Backup (\"The Peace of Mind\")

**Price: \$650--\$950**

Description

Entry-level digitization of all aircraft logbooks into searchable PDF/A
format with basic folder structure (Airframe, Engine, Propeller,
Avionics). Delivered on encrypted USB drive plus cloud download link.
Physical books returned in archival box.

Perfect For

Private Part 91 owners who have never digitized records and want
insurance against loss. The \"I should really do this\" customer.

What\'s Included

-   Complete digitization of 3--6 logbooks (Airframe, Engine, Propeller,
    plus accessories)

-   High-resolution scanning (300 DPI) with optical character
    recognition

-   Organized folder structure by log type

-   Kingston IronKey encrypted USB drive (32GB)

-   Secure cloud download link (30-day access)

-   Physical logbooks returned in archival storage box with acid-free
    dividers

Typical Turnaround

3--5 business days for typical single-engine piston aircraft (200--500
pages)

Pricing Detail

-   Single-engine piston (3--6 logbooks, 200--500 pages): \$650

-   Twin-engine piston (4--8 logbooks, 500--1,000 pages): \$850

-   Complex single (retractable gear, 6+ logbooks): \$950

Tier 2: Transaction Ready (\"The Sale Prep\")

**Price: \$1,200--\$5,000**

Description

Comprehensive digitization optimized for aircraft sale or purchase. Full
OCR searchable PDF/A of all logs, organized folder structure, 48-hour
priority turnaround, hyperlinked table of contents, and a shareable
\"Digital Closing Packet\" link (password-protected, time-expiring).
Includes brief cover memo summarizing total times, last annual date, and
AD compliance status.

Perfect For

Aircraft sellers listing with a broker, or brokers preparing a listing.
Triggered by the listing event.

What\'s Included

-   Everything in Tier 1, plus:

-   48-hour priority turnaround (single-engine) or 3--5 days
    (twin/turbine)

-   Hyperlinked table of contents for instant navigation

-   Shareable \"Digital Closing Packet\" with password protection

-   Time-expiring cloud link (customizable, typically 90 days)

-   Cover memo: total times, last annual, AD compliance summary

-   Professional presentation optimized for buyer due diligence

Typical Turnaround

24--48 hours (priority) for single-engine; 3--5 days for twins/turbines

Pricing Detail

-   Single-engine piston: \$1,200

-   Complex single/light twin: \$1,500

-   Twin-engine piston: \$2,000--\$2,500

-   Turboprop/light jet: \$3,000--\$5,000

Value proposition: This investment is 1.3--2.8% of a \$90,000
devaluation loss on a \$300,000 Mooney. For a \$1.5M turboprop
transaction, \$3,000 is 0.2% of the aircraft value.

Tier 3: Pre-Buy Inspection Support (\"The Buyer\'s Shield\")

**Price: \$1,500--\$4,000**

Description

Digitization commissioned by the buyer or buyer\'s mechanic during a
pre-buy inspection. Records are scanned at the inspection facility
(on-site capability), creating a searchable digital copy that the
buyer\'s A&P/IA can review remotely or on a tablet. Includes a
flagged-items memo noting any observed gaps: missing signatures,
incomplete AD entries, undocumented 337s, or absent 8130-3 forms.

Perfect For

Aircraft buyers and their designated inspectors conducting pre-buy
evaluations.

What\'s Included

-   On-site scanning at inspection facility

-   Same-day to 24-hour turnaround

-   Complete digitization with OCR searchability

-   Flagged-items memo identifying documentation gaps:

-   • Missing mechanic signatures or dates

-   • Incomplete AD compliance entries

-   • Undocumented FAA Form 337s (major alterations)

-   • Missing 8130-3 airworthiness approval tags

-   Tablet-ready format for mechanic review

-   Encrypted USB delivery + cloud link

Typical Turnaround

Same-day to 24-hour turnaround (on-site at inspection facility)

Pricing Detail

-   Single-engine piston: \$1,500

-   Complex single/light twin: \$2,000

-   Twin-engine piston: \$2,500--\$3,000

-   Turboprop/light jet: \$3,500--\$4,000

Premium justified by urgency, on-site travel, and the flagged-items
analysis. Pre-buy inspections create acute time pressure---the buyer
needs information fast to make a go/no-go decision.

Tier 4: Estate and Probate Records Service (\"The Executor\'s Toolkit\")

**Price: \$1,800--\$3,500**

Description

Specialized service for aircraft transferred through estate sales.
Includes physical inventory of all records found (often disorganized
boxes in a hangar or attic), condition assessment memo for the
executor/attorney, full digitization, and a \"Records Completeness
Report\" grading the documentation as Complete, Substantially Complete,
Incomplete, or Critically Deficient. Includes guidance on FAA
registration transfer requirements (AC Form 8050-1, 8050-2, Letters
Testamentary).

Perfect For

Estate executors, probate attorneys, heirs, and estate-sale brokers.
Referral channel: Kerr County/Kendall County/Gillespie County probate
attorneys.

What\'s Included

-   Physical inventory and assessment of all found records

-   Condition assessment memo for executor/attorney

-   Organization and cataloging of disorganized materials

-   Full digitization of all recoverable documents

-   Records Completeness Report with grading:

-   • Complete: All required logs present, continuous history

-   • Substantially Complete: Minor gaps, 90%+ coverage

-   • Incomplete: Significant gaps, 50--90% coverage

-   • Critically Deficient: Major gaps, \<50% coverage

-   FAA registration transfer guidance package

-   Recommendations for addressing documentation gaps

Typical Turnaround

5--10 business days (accounts for triage of disorganized records)

Pricing Detail

\$1,800--\$3,500 depending on record volume and condition. Premium
reflects the triage and assessment work, which is substantially more
labor-intensive than organized logbooks. Estate aircraft sales are among
the most documentation-challenged transactions in aviation. One-third of
aircraft transactions are delayed or cancelled due to maintenance data
issues---estate sales skew even worse. This service transforms a chaotic
situation into a structured, sellable package.

Tier 5: MRO Partnership Wholesale Tier (\"The Shop Rate\")

**Price: \$350--\$500 per annual-cycle scan**

Description

Standing agreement with maintenance shops. Provenarc Aero Solutions picks up
logbooks during annual inspections, scans new entries and any previously
unscanned material, and returns books before the annual is complete.
Shop receives a digital copy for its own records, reducing mechanic
research time on the next visit.

Perfect For

MRO shops and IA mechanics performing annuals and 100-hour inspections.
Anchor partner: Dugosh Aviation.

Pricing Detail

-   Wholesale shop rate: \$75/hour, or

-   Flat \$350--\$500 per annual-cycle scan (existing digital file
    update)

-   First-time full digitization referred by shop: standard pricing
    minus 15% shop referral discount

-   Referral fee to shop: \$50--\$75 per completed job

Tier 9: Subscription Maintenance (\"The Living Record\")

**Price: \$29--\$49/month**

Description

Monthly recurring service. After initial digitization, the owner emails
or mails photos/copies of new logbook entries (oil changes, annuals,
100-hours, repairs). Provenarc Aero Solutions scans, OCRs, and appends them to the
master digital file, maintaining a continuously current \"living
record.\"

Perfect For

Any owner who has completed initial digitization and wants to keep
records current without doing it themselves.

Pricing Detail

-   Basic (\$29/month): Up to 10 new pages/month, 48-hour turnaround

-   Premium (\$49/month): Unlimited pages plus quarterly AD compliance
    status review

This is the critical recurring revenue engine. At \$29--\$49/month per
subscriber, building a base of 50 subscribers by end of Year 2 generates
\$17,400--\$29,400/year in recurring revenue with minimal marginal cost
per update.

Tier 11: 8130-3 Extraction and Parts Traceability Database (\"The Parts
Ledger\")

**Price: \$1,500--\$3,000**

Description

AI-powered extraction of data from FAA Form 8130-3 Airworthiness
Approval Tags using intelligent document processing. Output: a
searchable Excel/database of all parts with Part Number, Serial Number,
Date, Releasing Authority, and Status. Hyperlinked to the scanned source
document in the master PDF.

Perfect For

Turbine aircraft owners, Part 135 operators, buyers conducting pre-buy
due diligence on high-value aircraft.

What\'s Included

-   AI extraction of all 8130-3 forms from logbooks

-   Manual verification of all extracted data

-   Searchable Excel database with fields:

-   • Part Number

-   • Serial Number

-   • Installation Date

-   • Releasing Authority (manufacturer/repair station)

-   • Status (serviceable, overhauled, etc.)

-   Hyperlinks to source document images

Typical Turnaround

5--10 business days (includes AI extraction plus manual verification of
all entries)

Pricing Detail

-   Standalone service: \$1,500--\$3,000

-   Bundled with full digitization package: 50% discount

This is the highest-value specialized service. A missing 8130-3 for a
single turbine blade set can cost \$50,000--\$200,000+ to recertify. The
ability to type a serial number and instantly retrieve the airworthiness
tag transforms the owner\'s records from a box of paper into a queryable
asset database.

